title: Gnalta, New South Wales
text:
Gnalta is a remote <a href="rural%20locality">rural locality</a> and <a href="Lands%20administrative%20divisions%20of%20Australia">civil parish</a> of <a href="Yungnulgra%20County">Yungnulgra County</a> in far North West <a href="New%20South%20Wales">New South Wales</a>.
Gnalta Station is a <a href="cattle%20station">homestead</a> on the Mount Wright Creek in northwest <a href="New%20South%20Wales">New South Wales</a>, about 550 km northeast of <a href="Adelaide%2C%20South%20Australia">Adelaide, South Australia</a> and 890 km <a href="north">north</a><a href="west">west</a> of <a href="Sydney%2C%20Australia">Sydney, Australia</a>.
History.
Silicified <a href="trilobite">trilobite</a>s <a href="fossil">fossil</a>s from the early middle <a href="Cambrian">Cambrian</a> have been found at Gnalta.
The Parish is on the traditional lands of the <a href="Wanjiwalku">Wandjiwalgu</a>. 
<a href="Australian%20Aboriginal">Aboriginal</a> peoples.
The station was at one time owned by <a href="Goldsbrough%20Mort%20%26amp%3B%20Co">Goldsbrough Mort and Company</a>.
Geography.
Gnalta is about 183<a href="meter">m</a> <a href="above%20sea%20level">above sea level</a>. although Gnalta Peak reaches about 270m above sea level.
The Parish has an <a href="arid">arid</a> landscape. and the nearest town is <a href="White%20Cliffs%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">Whitecliffs</a>.
The parish has extremely hot <a href="summer">summer</a>s and mild <a href="winter">winter</a>s. Summers would usually exceed 36 °C. Winters are usually around 17<a href="Degree%20centigrade">°C</a>. The annual average <a href="rainfall">rainfall</a> is which would make it a <a href="semi-arid%20climate">semi-arid climate</a> except that its high <a href="evapotranspiration">evapotranspiration</a>, or its aridity, makes it a <a href="desert%20climate">desert climate</a>. The parish has a <a href="K%C3%B6ppen%20climate%20classification">Köppen climate classification</a> of BWh (Hot desert). is almost unpopulated, with less than two inhabitants per square kilometer.
The nearest town is the <a href="village">village</a> of <a href="White%20Cliffs%2C%20New%20South%20Wales">White Cliffs, New South Wales</a>.
